title: Sydney woman sells everything she owns to travel world - Daily Mail
text: Woman sick of 'the whole grown up thing' is selling EVERYTHING she owns including her $20,000 wedding ring so she can escape Australia after her marriage breakdown Sydney woman Jade Green is selling everything she owns after a breakup Ms Green took to Facebook on Friday to advertise $30,000 worth of goods She is selling everything from a bird cage to her $20,000 wedding ring Published: 05:22 GMT, 27 January 2017 | Updated: 05:22 GMT, 27 January 2017 69 shares comments A Sydney woman is selling 'everything she owns' so she can travel the world after a marriage breakdown. Jade Green took to Facebook on Friday to advertise $30,000 worth of goods, including her $20,000 engagement ring. 'Off to travel the world so I am selling EVERYTHING I OWN,' Ms Green wrote in the group Bondi Local Loop. Jade Green (pictured) took to Facebook on Friday to advertise $30,000 worth of goods A Sydney woman is selling 'everything she owns' including her $20,000 engagement ring (pictured) 'Off to travel the world so I am selling EVERYTHING I OWN,' Ms Green wrote in group Bondi Local Loop 'I am sick of adulting and want a refund on the whole grown up thing.' In the post she explained she doesn't want to come back to her old life and wants to 'start fresh.' 'I have some really nice things but it represents a past marriage and the old me,' she wrote.
